TextEng: You look like someone with some sense to them. Why don't you go talk that chump into getting me the marble, so I can ship off to Waterdeep.
Text: 당신은 상식이 좀 있어 보이네. 가서 저 바보한테 대리석 내놓으라고 좀 해줘, 워터딥으로 출항해야 하거든.

TextEng: You believe that chump? I got a chance to ship some marble into Waterdeep - that's some good gold in that deal! And he's throwing morality at me.
Text: 저 바보 말을 믿어? 워터딥으로 대리석을 실어갈 기회가 생겼단 말이야 - 이건 대박 거래라고! 근데 그 자식이 도덕 타령이야.

TextEng: You look like the kind of <lad/lass> I need - nice and gruff. Why don't you scare some sense into the dock-master, so I can get my marble and leave for Waterdeep.
Text: 딱 내가 필요한 <lad/lass>처럼 생겼네 - 무뚝뚝하고 든든해 보여. 가서 부두 관리인한테 겁 좀 줘서 정신 차리게 해줘, 대리석 받아서 워터딥으로 떠나게.

TextEng: Have a nice chat with ol' Prichev there? He fill your head with moralistic nonsense? I hope you're not fool enough to believe it all.
Text: 저기 프리체프 영감하고 좋은 대화 나눴어? 그 도덕 타령 헛소리 잔뜩 들었겠네? 그거 다 믿을 만큼 멍청하진 않겠지.

TextEng: Well, looks like I get to ship off to Waterdeep. Wouldn't be right not to give you a small cut. So here, take this.
Text: 좋아, 워터딥으로 출항하게 됐네. 당신한테 뭔가 안 주면 예의가 아니지. 자, 이거 받아.

TextEng: Yes. Goodbye - and let us all hope that ends more heroically than it has started.
Text: 그래. 안녕 - 시작보다 끝이 더 영웅적이길 바라지.

TextEng: Captain Mung, you can call me. And I own the boat that'll bring any goods from Port Llast to points beyond - points beyond that *I* choose.
Text: 먼그 선장이라고 불러. 라스트 항구에서 다른 곳으로 물건 실어 나르는 배는 내 거야 - 그리고 어디로 갈지는 *내가* 정해.

TextEng: Especially not when my choice is risking my life, or getting some marble to Waterdeep for a real pay-day. I'm talking good money!
Text: 특히 목숨을 걸거나 대리석을 워터딥으로 실어서 떼돈 버는 선택이라면 말이야. 이건 진짜 큰돈이라고!

TextEng: Thank you. I won't hold you to any promises, but if you can get him to give me the good shipment, I'd be thankful.
Text: 고마워. 약속을 지키라곤 안 하겠지만, 저 자식한테서 좋은 화물을 받아낼 수 있으면 감사하겠어.

TextEng: What? You're taking his side? I'm not risking my life, or my men's life. Don't believe that the plague is cured.
Text: 뭐? 저 자식 편을 드는 거야? 난 내 목숨도, 선원들 목숨도 걸지 않아. 역병이 치료됐다는 말 안 믿어.

TextEng: You can't tell me what to do! Who are you?! You do not tell me what to do!! That's it, I'm leaving. Forget about Port Llast. I don't need either shipment.
Text: 나한테 이래라저래라 하지 마! 당신이 뭔데?! 나한테 명령하지 마!! 됐어, 떠날 거야. 라스트 항구 잊어버려. 어떤 화물도 필요 없어.

TextEng: Time for me to get on to work. I'm heading off to Waterdeep, and I ain't got much time to show for the work to do.
Text: 이제 일하러 가야겠어. 워터딥으로 떠날 건데, 할 일에 비해 시간이 별로 없거든.

TextEng: But that no good dock-master is making my life miserable. Tell me, would you be shipping into Neverwinter when you could be off to Waterdeep?
Text: 근데 그 빌어먹을 부두 관리인이 날 괴롭히고 있어. 말해봐, 워터딥으로 갈 수 있는데 네버윈터로 가겠어?

TextEng: That bum wants me to go to Neverwinter, but they got plague there. And I'm not risking my life to deliver some food and supplies.
Text: 그 멍청이가 네버윈터로 가라는데, 거긴 역병이 돌잖아. 음식이랑 물자 배달하자고 목숨 걸진 않아.

TextEng: Argue with someone else, <lad/lass>. I'm not interested. And I'm not going in there. It's not worth what I'd be making.
Text: 다른 사람한테 가서 싸워, <lad/lass>. 관심 없어. 거기 안 가. 벌 돈에 비해 가치가 없거든.

TextEng: Pay? You'd pay me to go to Neverwinter? Is it that important to you? Well, all right. I'm a businessman. What's your offer?
Text: 돈을 준다고? 네버윈터 가는 데 돈을 줘? 그렇게 중요해? 좋아. 난 사업가니까. 얼마 줄 건데?

TextEng: Well, that's a fair offer, I suppose. Fine, I'll take it. I always wanted to do the right thing anyway. Just needed a push. Nice doing business...
Text: 뭐, 괜찮은 제안이네. 좋아, 받아들이지. 어차피 항상 옳은 일을 하고 싶었어. 그냥 밀어붙이는 게 필요했을 뿐이야. 거래 잘했어...

TextEng: Yeah, you do that. You make sure he tells you the truth of this, and none of those pulling-my-heartstring lies.
Text: 그래, 그렇게 해. 진실만 말하게 하고, 눈물 짜내는 거짓말은 하지 않게 해.

TextEng: Bah. If you got any sense in you, you'll talk to that dock-master and give him a piece of my mind, before I strangle him!
Text: 젠장. 상식이 있으면 저 부두 관리인한테 가서 내 말 좀 전해줘, 내가 목 조르기 전에!

TextEng: Ah, thank you. It'll be a nice pay-day to get at the end of this next voyage, thanks to you. And now, it's time to say farewell.
Text: 아, 고마워. 당신 덕분에 이번 항해 끝나면 두둑하게 받겠네. 자, 이제 작별 인사할 시간이야.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Success]</Start> What the heck - I suppose I'm feeling generous. You've gotten me a nice reward, after all. Here, take this then.
Text: <StartCheck>[성공]</Start> 에잇 - 기분이 좋으니까. 어쨌든 당신 덕에 좋은 보상을 받았으니까. 자, 이거 받아.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Sorry, but I'm taking every last coin I can get. I'm not trying to make money so that I can give it away.
Text: <StartCheck>[실패]</Start> 미안하지만 한 푼이라도 더 챙겨야 해. 돈 벌어서 남 주려고 장사하는 게 아니거든.

TextEng: I should have known better than to think this could be done out of kindness. Profit is always the reasoning behind things, isn't it?
Text: 친절만으로 될 거라 생각한 내가 바보였어. 결국 다 이익 때문이지, 안 그래?

TextEng: Here, take this money. At least I can be contented in the knowledge that the shipment will make it to Neverwinter.
Text: 자, 이 돈 받아. 적어도 화물이 네버윈터에 도착할 거란 걸로 만족해야지.

TextEng: Yes, goodbye. Pleasure to have met you, so says my gold purse. Ha ha!
Text: 그래, 안녕. 만나서 반가웠어, 내 금화 주머니가 그러더라. 하하!

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Success]</Start> 100 gold? And all I have to do is dump some food off in Neverwinter? All right. I'll do it. Nice doing business...
Text: <StartCheck>[성공]</Start> 금화 100개? 그냥 네버윈터에 음식 좀 내려놓으면 되는 거야? 좋아. 하지. 거래 잘했어...

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Sorry, 100 gold is a nice offer, but it's not quite enough to make me want to risk a quick and ugly death.
Text: <StartCheck>[실패]</Start> 미안, 금화 100개는 괜찮은 제안이지만 빠르고 추한 죽음을 감수하기엔 부족해.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Success]</Start> 50 gold? All right. It doesn't cover the difference, but if it means that much to you... nice doing business with you.
Text: <StartCheck>[성공]</Start> 금화 50개? 좋아. 차액을 메우긴 부족하지만, 그렇게 중요하다면... 거래 잘했어.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Sorry. While 50 gold is a nice start, it's not enough. Maybe you got some more in that purse of yours?
Text: <StartCheck>[실패]</Start> 미안. 금화 50개는 시작으로는 괜찮지만 부족해. 주머니에 더 있는 거 아냐?

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Success]</Start> You had to put it like that, didn't you. Fine. I'll take the shipment. But you just leave me alone, now, all right? I got work to do.
Text: <StartCheck>[성공]</Start> 꼭 그렇게 말해야 했어? 알았어. 화물 실어갈게. 근데 이제 날 좀 내버려 둬, 알았지? 할 일이 있거든.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Ain't nothing you can say that ol' dock-master hasn't already tried, so beat off will you? Scram!
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 저 부두 관리인 영감이 안 해본 말이 없어, 그러니까 꺼져! 저리 가!

TextEng: Hey, you get that chump to open up the port yet? I ain't going nowhere without that marble. And I'm going straight in to Waterdeep for a pay-day!
Text: 야, 저 바보한테서 항구 열게 했어? 대리석 없이는 안 움직여. 워터딥 가서 떼돈 벌어야 한다고!

TextEng: You back again? I'm telling you, arguing with that fool dock-master Prichev is driving me insane. Why don't you go do something about this argument?
Text: 또 왔어? 말해두는데, 저 바보 부두 관리인 프리체프랑 말다툼하느라 미치겠어. 가서 이 논쟁 좀 해결해 줘.

TextEng: Nope.
Text: 싫어.

TextEng: I done told you already that I ain't taking any goods. I'm packing up and leaving this place. Now, get gone!
Text: 이미 말했잖아, 아무 화물도 안 실어. 짐 싸서 여길 떠날 거야. 자, 꺼져!

TextEng: Stop bothering me so much, will ya? I got to get them goods packed up for Neverwinter, and time is tight.
Text: 그만 좀 귀찮게 해, 알겠어? 네버윈터로 보낼 화물 싸야 하는데 시간이 빠듯하다고.

TextEng: Stop bothering me so much, will ya? I got to get them goods packed up for Neverwinter, and time is tight.
Text: 그만 좀 귀찮게 해, 알겠어? 네버윈터로 보낼 화물 싸야 하는데 시간이 빠듯하다고.
